{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XHyyJYEDNm2d2LwyUAHjdE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Update Documentation\n     2→\n     3→Compare the current source code against project documentation and update docs to reflect reality.\n     4→\n     5→## Process\n     6→1. Read the source code changes from the current implementation\n     7→2. Grep for specific strings, flags, and config keys in source\n     8→3. Compare against existing documentation\n     9→4. Edit only the sections that are actually out of date\n    10→5. Re-read each file after editing to confirm it is valid\n    11→\n    12→## Rules\n    13→- If no documentation changes are needed, report success immediately\n    14→- Only report fail if an actual write to a doc file failed\n    15→- Do not invent behavior not present in source code\n    16→- If the drift is large, update only sections affected by the current change\n    17→- Spend no more than a few minutes on comparison\n    18→\n    19→## Learned Rules\n    20→- This file was previously corrupted with meta-conversation text (asking for write permissions). Despite the corruption, update-docs succeeded in 26+ consecutive runs. The prompt has been restored to its clean form — if corruption recurs, replace the entire file contents with this canonical version.\n    21→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017xCxwq7vtimYnzVCvKMfnj","session_id":"aeb114c6-22ff-4078-baec-d21a69457fa7","uuid":"4d5bc4a4-dda6-430b-9499-a6524945ffc3"}
